    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Low, bench-like seats or kneelers used for prayer or meditation. Known in many cultures, including in Christianity and indigenous African cultures. For specifically Western Christian prayer furniture, 'prie-dieu (benches)' and 'prie-dieu chairs' are sometimes called 'prayer stools.'</Note_Text>
